<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1554">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/392a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Telegraph immediately whether Porras and Díaz themselves favor American
                            supervision of registration and election, so that the request is in fact
                            made by the Government and both political parties. Do you recommend our
                            acquiescence? Could a committee, consisting of yourself as chairman,
                            Colonel Goethals and Governor Thatcher, devise suitable measures after
                            consulting the Government and both parties?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>